    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are facing a challenging slate today, navigating a gauntlet of elite arms, but **Jackson Merrill** stands out as the clear offensive anchor with a massive 75.27 score. His matchup against Feltner is our most favorable pairing, bolstered by a significant +14% park factor and a +15% boost from facing a high-xERA pitcher. While **Kyle Tucker** (52.03) and **Drake Baldwin** (60.73) provide necessary stability, **Jackson Merrill** is the primary driver for our Roto categories, especially given his favorable positioning in the three-hole, which optimizes his chances for both RBI and Run production against a vulnerable rotation spot.\n\nWe are forced to be tactical with our lineup construction due to the presence of high-end arms like deGrom and Webb. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (56.38) earns a start despite a tough matchup against Ritchie, as his dynamic platoon splits and premium spot in the order outweigh the skill of the opposing pitcher. Conversely, **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Marcell Ozuna** face aggressive headwinds; **Marcell Ozuna** is hampered by a difficult matchup against deGrom and a suboptimal BvP history, resulting in a marginal 43.30 score. The most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Jung**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a 39.89 score. While he projects as a solid contributor, the optimizer leaned toward the specific lineup efficiencies of **Dominic Smith** and **Nasim Nunez**, as the depth of our bench remains taxed by the ongoing absence of **Jordan Westburg** on the IL and scheduled off-days for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Gunnar Henderson**.\n\nRisk management remains paramount today, particularly with **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Andy Pages** facing pitchers who prioritize high-efficiency, slow deliveries, which historically dampens our stolen base upside. We are keeping a close eye on the official confirmation for **Marcell Ozuna**, as any shift downward in the batting order would further erode his already thin projection. With **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Coby Mayo**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Brady House**, and **Liam Hicks** currently held in reserve, we are prepared to pivot should late-breaking lineup news or inclement weather reports shift the projected efficiency scores throughout the afternoon.",
